{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox terrorist attack |title=2012 Afar region tourist attack |image= Afar in Ethiopia.svg |caption= Map of Ethiopia showing Afar Region |location=[[Erta Ale]], [[Afar Region]], [[Ethiopia]] |target= |date=17 January 2012 |time-begin= |time-end= |timezone=UTC+3 |type=[[Shooting]] |fatalities=5 |injuries=3 |victims=4 [[Kidnap|kidnapped]] |susperps=[[Afar Revolutionary Democratic Unity Front]] |perps= }} {{Campaignbox Second Afar insurgency}}
The '''2012 Afar region tourist attack''' was a shooting incident on the night of 17 January 2012 at [[Erta Ale]] volcano in the [[Afar Region]] of [[Ethiopia]] which killed 5 and injured 3. Four people were kidnapped in the attack.
Bereket Simon, the country's communications minister told ''[[Reuters]]'' the attack was carried out at 5&nbsp;am on 17 January, by Eritrean-trained groups. Two foreigners, a driver, and a policeman were kidnapped. [[Eritrea]] denied having trained and armed the attackers.<ref> {{cite news |title = Ethiopia says four kidnapped in Afar tourist attack |url = http://afriport.hu/angol-nyelv-hirek/11585-ethiopia-says-four-kidnapped-in-afar-tourist-attack.html |archive-url = https://archive.is/20130218002816/http://afriport.hu/angol-nyelv-hirek/11585-ethiopia-says-four-kidnapped-in-afar-tourist-attack.html |dead-url = yes |archive-date = 18 February 2013 |work = [[Reuters]] |date = 18 January 2012 |accessdate = 2012-01-21 }}</ref>
It was later revealed that two [[German people|German]]s, two [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]]s and an [[Austrian people|Austrian]] were killed in the attack. Two Germans and two [[Ethiopian people|Ethiopian]]s were kidnapped. Three people injured: two [[Belgians]] and a Hungarian.<ref>{{cite news | title = Ethiopia: Tourists kidnapped after deadly Afar attack | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-16610890 | work = [[BBC News]] | date = 18 January 2012 | accessdate = 2012-01-21 }}</ref> The Germans were released 7 March the same year.<ref>[http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/regions/africa/120307/ethiopia-rebels-release-german-kidnap-victims "Ethiopian rebels release Germans kidnapped in Afar desert]"<nowiki>. GlobalPost, 7 March 2012. Retrieved 2013-7-3.</nowiki>. [https://www.webcitation.org/6I4e3Jk2X?url=http://www.globalpost.com/dispatch/news/regions/africa/120307/ethiopia-rebels-release-german-kidnap-victims Archived] 2013-07-13.</ref>
