'''''Nature and Culture''''' is a [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Berghahn Books]] that covers the historical and contemporary relationships that [[society|societies]] have with [[nature]]. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Sing C. Chew and [[Matthias Gross]]. The publication themes include cultural reactions and conceptions of nature, [[ecological restoration]], ecological time, as well as political and socio-technical arrangements of landscapes.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://journals.berghahnbooks.com/_uploads/nc/NC_Themes.pdf |format=PDF |title=Nature+ Culture Publication Themes |publisher=Journals.berghahnbooks.com |accessdate=2015-07-03}}</ref> Some new directions of the journal include [[environmental technology|environmental technologies]] and [[renewable energy]] cultures.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/berghahn/natcult/2014/00000009/00000002 |title=Nature and Culture: ingentaconnect Table Of Contents |publisher=Ingentaconnect.com |date= |accessdate=2015-07-03}}</ref>
==Indexing and abstracting== ''Nature and Culture'' is indexed and abstracted in: {{columns-list|colwidth=30em| *Abstracts in Anthropology *[[Annual Bibliography of English Language and Literature]] *Anthropological Index *[[British Humanities Index]] *[[International Bibliography of the Social Sciences]] *[[International Bibliography of Periodical Literature]] *[[Sociological Abstracts]] *[[Scopus]] *[[Social Sciences Citation Index]] *[[Current Contents]]/Social and Behavioral Sciences *[[TOC Premier]] }}
